Challenges (League of Legends)

Edit
  • Edit source
  • View history
  • Move
  • Purge
  • Talk (0)
  • Watch

Challenges are cost-free achievements in League of Legends that allow players to chase unique objectives and enhance customization of their profiles.[1][2]

Overview[]

All Challenges are tracked within the Challenges tab in the League client, players earn Challenge Points to progress a challenge by doing any number of tasks while playing the game. Challenge Points accumulate from completing individual objectives on a Challenge Card. Challenges Points are added to your total Category points, which contribute to your Crystal rank and Challenge-group Capstones.

Challenge Cards all build up to their group’s "Capstone" Challenge. You can only fully master a Capstone Challenge by completing all the other Challenges within its group. When you add up all the Challenge Points, Capstones, and Categories together you get your Crystal rank. This is what displays on your profile and summarizes your overall Challenges mastery to whoever visits, ranked from Unranked to Challenger. Your Crystal rank will display on your profile border, lobby and loading screen.

Challenges are divided into 5 main categories.
Expertise: Challenges focused on skillfully outmatching your opponents.
Veterancy: Challenges focused on lifetime stats.
Collection: Challenges focused on collecting cosmetics and engaging with loot.
Imagination: Challenges focused on game modes and innovative plays.
Teamwork & Strategy: Challenges focused on teamplay.

There is also the Legacy category, which focuses on season-based accomplishments and past achievements that can no longer be obtained. These do not contribute to your overall Challenge progress, nor can you level up Legacy as a category.

Identity[]

A Challenge is identified by its Token, a unique icon that represents that challenge, as well as its current rank. The Token is at the center of every Challenge Card, below the Token is the challenge's name and its criteria. The upper left-hand corner shows you how many points a challenge is contributing toward your overall Challenges score. The upper right-hand corner shows you which modes a challenge can be earned in. Challenges can be labeled as ARAM only or Summoner's Rift only, but they are actually game mode specific, as demonstrated by the Co-op vs AI challenges. The bottom of the card shows the next major reward you'll receive for leveling the challenge up to a given tier.

You can equip up to three tokens. Tokens are displayed on your profile and in the Lobby and the Loading Screen. They can be hovered over to see its associated challenge and tier. Titles are special names earned by leveling certain challenges to specific tiers, you can freely choose between any title you've unlocked. Titles are displayed on your profile as well as in the Lobby and Loading Screen.

Leaderboard[]

Once you rank a token to Master tier, hovering it will also display a leaderboard that compares your progress to everyone else's on the same server. You can also hover your friends' tokens to see their challenge progress as well. To be on the Grandmaster or Challenger tier Leaderboard, you need to both clear the Challenge a certain number of times AND be in the top percentage of players in the server.

To reach Grandmaster, you must be in the top 25% of players who have also achieved Master and be above the Grandmaster threshold. To reach Challenger, you must be in the top 5% of players who have also achieved Master and be above the Challenger threshold. Ladders are recalculated every 24 hours.

All challenges with a Challenger threshold have a leaderboard, except for Malfunction and Well-Rounded Traveller.

Trivia[]

  • On the launch of Challenges (V12.9), there was a bug forcing the "Challenges Are Here!" introductory pop-up appear every time a player logged into the client. The annoying message persisted for 3 months, until the bug was eventually fixed. As a gratitude for patience, all affected players could receive an eponymous limited-time challenge by logging in between V12.18 and V12.20.
